or%20a%20new%20role%20externally.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20start%20to%20finish%2C%20it%20can%20take%20up%20to%20six%20months%20to%20receive%20an%20offer%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20first%20step%20in%20the%20application%20process%20is%20pretty%20standard%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20typically%20responds%20to%20a%20successful%20application%20by%20setting%20up%20an%20interview%20with%20a%20recruiter%20or%20a%20human%20resources%20employee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20engineers%20said%20they%20secured%20an%20initial%20interview%20by%20either%20sending%20their%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20into%20an%20application%20on%20Tesla's%20careers%20page%2C%20chatting%20with%20a%20Tesla%20representative%20at%20a%20networking%20event%2C%20or%20having%20a%20colleague%20pass%20along%20their%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20through%20the%20company's%20internal%20recommendation%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%20it%20really%20is%20who%20you%20know%20at%20Tesla%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20engineer%20who%20has%20worked%20at%20the%20company%20for%20six%20years.%20%26quot%3BIt%20helps%20to%20go%20to%20a%20feeder%20college%20where%20a%20classmate%20can%20help%20recommend%20you%20for%20a%20role.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecruiters%20often%20sift%20through%20thousands%20of%20applications%2C%20only%20giving%20interviews%20to%20up%20to%2020%20or%20so%20applicants%2C%20according%20to%20four%20engineers%20who've%20been%20involved%20in%20the%20hiring%20process.%20Only%20about%20half%20of%20those%20candidates%20make%20it%20to%20the%20next%20step%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22tesla%20fremont%20factory%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61e9ec4d2b43ff00185dee15%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22664%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETesla%20employs%20over%20140%2C000%20people%20globally.%3Cp%3EJustin%20Sullivan%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20initial%20culture%20fit%20interview%20%E2%80%94%20which%20includes%20traditional%20questions%20about%20why%20people%20want%20to%20work%20at%20Tesla%20and%20how%20they%20jibe%20with%20others%20%E2%80%94%20candidates%20who%20progress%20typically%20chat%20separately%20with%20a%20manager%20and%20at%20least%20one%20engineer%20from%20their%20prospective%20team.%20These%20interviews%20are%20more%20technical%20and%20sometimes%20include%20a%20take-home%20or%20live%20test.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTesla%20takes%20a%20no-bullshit%20approach%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20engineer%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BAt%20other%20companies%2C%20you%20can%20sometimes%20get%20away%20with%20saying%20something%20to%20sound%20impressive.%20You%20can't%20do%20that%20at%20Tesla.%20If%20you%20don't%20know%20something%2C%20own%20up%20to%20it%20because%20they%20will%20always%20ask%20the%20follow-up%20questions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPanel%20interviews%20can%20be%20up%20to%20six%20hours%20long%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20step%20in%20Tesla's%20hiring%20process%20includes%20a%20presentation%20and%20a%20series%20of%20rapid-fire%20interviews%20that%20can%20take%20anywhere%20from%20four%20to%20six%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApplicants%20are%20typically%20told%20to%20present%20on%20a%20previous%20project%20for%2015-30%20minutes%2C%20followed%20by%20a%20Q%26amp%3BA%20session%20on%20the%20project.%20Tesla%20workers%20said%20it's%20best%20for%20early-career%20applicants%20to%20present%20on%20college%20group%20projects%20or%20personal%20ventures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%20four%20to%20six%20engineers%20sit%20in%20on%20the%20presentation%20and%20later%20break%20off%20to%20interview%20the%20candidate%20on%20their%20own%20for%20about%2030%20minutes%20each.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20try%20to%20leave%20it%20pretty%20open-ended%20because%20it's%20a%20good%20way%20to%20find%20red%20flags%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20engineer%2C%20whose%20been%20involved%20in%20the%20recruiting%20process%2C%20said%20regarding%20the%20presentation%20prompt.%20%26quot%3BWe%20tell%20them%20not%20to%20present%20something%20confidential%20and%20that's%20the%20biggest%20red%20flag%20if%20they%20present%20something%20like%20that.%20It's%20an%20easy%20no%20if%20we%20know%20they%20won't%20be%20trustworthy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Tesla%20engineers%20said%20they%20spent%20over%2040%20hours%20preparing%20for%20the%20presentation%20over%20the%20course%20of%20several%20weeks.%20The%20panel%20can%20take%20place%20over%20Zoom%20or%20in%20person.%20It%20also%20includes%20a%20short%20break%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20session%20to%20give%20panelists%20time%20to%20take%20lunch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224633%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20logo%20marks%20the%20showroom%20and%20service%20center%20for%20the%20US%20automotive%20and%20energy%20company%20Tesla%20in%20Amsterdam%20on%20October%2023%2C%202019%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6586a44fab6f2ebb11f69f8c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223202%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETesla%20received%20over%203.6%20millions%20applications%20in%202022.%3Cp%3EJOHN%20THYS%20%2F%20Getty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20need%20to%20make%20sure%20you%20know%20the%20technical%20details%20of%20your%20project%20inside%20and%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20engineer%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20the%20most%20complicated%20tech%20so%20long%20as%20you%20can%20talk%20about%20what%20you've%20done%20in%20great%20detail.%20You%20need%20to%20be%20able%20to%20tell%20them%20why%20you%20approached%20it%20the%20way%20you%20did%20and%20address%20other%20ways%20of%20accomplishing%20it%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20panel%2C%20the%20employees%20meet%20to%20give%20a%20%26quot%3Bblind%20vote%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20candidate%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20the%20panelists%20all%20submit%20their%20scores%20at%20once%20%E2%80%94one%20engineer%20with%20knowledge%20of%20the%20process%20said.%20Candidates%20are%20scored%20on%20a%20scale%20of%20one%20to%20four.%20If%20a%20single%20panel%20member%20gives%20the%20candidate%20a%20score%20of%20one%20and%20can%20back%20up%20their%20opinion%2C%20the%20individual's%20application%20is%20usually%20rejected%2C%20while%20a%20score%20of%20a%20three%20or%20a%20four%20is%20viewed%20as%20a%20sign%20of%20approval%20for%20the%20prospective%20hire%2C%20the%20engineer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnly%20about%20half%20the%20applicants%20who%20make%20it%20to%20the%20panel%20stage%20are%20selected%2C%20two%20engineers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESit%20tight%20%E2%80%94%20it%20could%20six%20months%20to%20land%20the%20job%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDepending%20on%20the%20role%2C%20some%20applicants%20are%20offered%20the%20job%20after%20a%20successful%20panel%20interview.%20For%20higher%20level%20positions%2C%20the%20candidates%20can%20go%20on%20to%20interview%20with%20director%20or%20VP-level%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20applicants%20are%20required%20to%20fill%20out%20a%20form%20that%20will%20be%20sent%20to%20a%20VP%20or%20director-level%20worker%20outlining%20three%20reasons%20they%20would%20be%20a%20good%20fit%20for%20Tesla%2C%20three%20workers%20said.%20Some%20of%20the%20notes%20are%20even%20passed%20onto%20Musk%2C%20the%20engineers%20said.%20Last%20year%2C%20the%20Tesla%20CEO%20said%20in%20an%20email%20to%20staff%20that%20he%20must%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-email-tesla-approve-new-hires-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapprove%20all%20new%20hires%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20start%20to%20finish%2C%20the%20entire%20process%20can%20take%20anywhere%20from%20one%20to%20six%20months%2C%20the%20engineers%20said.%20Seven%20engineers%20said%20that%20Tesla%20had%20the%20most%20intensive%20application%20process%20they'd%20seen%20in%20the%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHalf%20the%20time%20we%20miss%20out%20because%20we're%20too%20slow%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20engineer%20with%20knowledge%20of%20the%20hiring%20process%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20know%20it%20but%20it's%20set%20up%20in%20some%20ways%20to%20find%20the%20people%20who%20are%20so%20gung-ho%20they're%20willing%20to%20wait.%20They're%20people%20who'd%20probably%20get%20a%20higher%20base%20pay%20at%20a%20different%20company%2C%20but%20they%20have%20the%20opportunity%20to%20cash%20in%20on%20Tesla%20stock%20too.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Tesla%20spokesperson%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20work%20for%20Tesla%20or%20have%20insight%20to%20share%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20the%20reporter%20from%20a%20non-work%20email%20and%20device%20at%20gkay%40insider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-hired-at-tesla-job-interview-process%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709457661000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ddf83890413ab8e1d71451%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-hired-at-tesla-job-interview-process%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%2210%20Tesla%20engineers%20break%20down%20the%20interview%20process%20and%20give%20tips%20on%20getting%20a%20job%20at%20Elon%20Musk's%20company.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22gkay%40insider.com%20(Grace%20Kay)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A169%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-hired-at-tesla-job-interview-process%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Vedanta%20Resources%20to%20deleverage%20debt%20by%20%243%20billion%20over%203%20years%3A%20Official%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709457654000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2020-12%2F29%2Ffull%2F1609235533-0889.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews