roductions%20that%20helped%20place%20%3Cem%3EPlay%20with%20a%20Cobra%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20the%20canon%20of%20Indian%20theatre%20and%20stagecraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20play%E2%80%99s%20premiere%20in%20Kannada%20in%201989%20was%20directed%20by%20Shankar%20Nag.%20Pinty%20herself%20played%20Rani%20in%20the%20first%20five%20shows%2C%20and%20her%20sister%20Arundathi%20Nag%20played%20Kathe%20(the%20Story).%20In%20the%20next%20five%20shows%2C%20the%20sisters%20swapped%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPinty%20told%20us%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20shows%20were%20performed%20outdoors%20at%20Chitra%20Kala%20Parishad%20in%20Bangalore.%20Mattresses%20were%20hired%20for%20audiences%20to%20be%20seated%20on.%20However%2C%20when%20the%20shows%20went%20full%2C%20we%20even%20had%20people%20sitting%20on%20the%20huge%20trees%20out%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%2C%20there%20were%20people%20who%20had%20come%20from%20out%20of%20town%20and%20could%20not%20get%20seats%3B%20so%20we%20did%20an%20extra%20show%20on%20the%20same%20day%20%E2%80%94%20impromptu%2C%20with%20no%20publicity%20%E2%80%94%20which%20also%20ended%20up%20being%20full.%20We%20had%20used%20puppets%20for%20the%20snake%20and%20the%20dog%20which%20were%20handled%20by%20puppeteers%20on%20a%20concealed%20catwalk.%20That%20was%20where%20they%20swung%20the%20lit%20lamps%20from%20%E2%80%94%20which%20had%20to%20have%20mustard%20oil%20so%20they%20would%20not%20go%20off%20in%20the%20wind.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20cast%20included%20B.%20Jayashri%2C%20Ramesh%20Bhat%2C%20and%20Shankar%20Nag%20himself.%20It%20was%20scored%20by%20C.%20Ashwath%2C%20with%20a%20spectacular%20song%2C%20%E2%80%9CMaayada%20Manada%20Bhara%E2%80%9D%20written%20by%20Gopal%20Vajpeyi.%20Listen%20to%20a%20rendition%20of%20the%20song%20by%20Pallavi%20MD%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fci3.googleusercontent.com%2Fmeips%2FADKq_NYuodSvGkCiQjEtAD16PM6XTMGkiNh50cdfXioKy-LB37Xr9t-nwTG2daFsVDxA5yoaOseP1bEC1LxlrEcK_N1FXGutjbw3usCWZTWaOmxoPh9CGuhXAal626Jwan4UENl7pw9wdGFIfYu7HafEV3qM-YQyafgtO5a1eNcQJ2eai3Cbh4vX5lJKGSELVZvLC1bjuu1LkJHUlFWyu_hXKuDd9yUnM6m0CS13HUc9OV4yJtOGqLqn4zRwyP72psSqRoN4ZC6oTcZueAAMeg27dCdXz6Q7Dp8usiO6vc9e8rajQ96nOPI81i9exA%3Ds0-d-e1-ft%23https%3A%2F%2Fsubstackcdn.com%2Fimage%2Ffetch%2Fw_1456%2Cc_limit%2Cf_auto%2Cq_auto%3Agood%2Cfl_progressive%3Asteep%2Fhttps%253A%252F%252Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%252Fpublic%252Fimages%252F48aaa770-2fe0-4c7c-9525-9817e5fd82ec_1456x474.png%5C%22%20tabindex%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221456%5C%22%20data-bit%3D%5C%22iit%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22474%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EShankar%20Nag%E2%80%99s%20Nagamandala%20(1989)%2C%20with%20Rani%20played%20by%20Pinty%20Rao%20(left%20and%20centre)%20and%20Arundathi%20Nag%20(right).%20Photo%3A%20Ranga%20Shankara.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20New%20Delhi%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20Neelam%20Mansingh%20Chowdhry%20was%20creating%20a%20production%20in%20Punjabi%20that%20she%20would%20breathe%20life%20into%20again%20and%20again%20over%20the%20next%20three%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENaga%20Chhaya%20(1990)%20drew%20on%20the%20naqqal%20folk%20tradition%2C%20casting%20a%20mix%20of%20its%20performers%20alongside%20city-based%20actors.%20The%20play%20was%20translated%20by%20the%20eminent%20poet%20Surjit%20Patar%2C%20and%20scored%20by%20BV%20Karanth%2C%20using%20a%20medley%20of%20instruments%20and%20vocals%20unusual%20for%20theatre%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuresh%20Awasthi%2C%20in%20a%20review%20of%20the%20play%2C%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%98Naga%20Chhaya%E2%80%99%20represents%20the%20best%20of%20%E2%80%98new%E2%80%99%20contemporary%20theatre%2C%20a%20%E2%80%98theatre%20of%20roots%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%A6%20Watching%20%5Bit%5D%20is%20seeing%20a%20segment%20of%20Punjab%E2%80%99s%20rich%20traditional%20performance%20culture%20%E2%80%94%20rhythms%2C%20colours%2C%20sounds%2C%20designs%2C%20gestures%20and%20postures.%20It%20is%20like%20reading%20a%20cultural%20document.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKarnad%20watched%20the%20Company%20production%20at%20Kamani%20Theatre%2C%20and%20he%20loved%20it.%20According%20to%20Neelam%20Mansingh%2C%20he%20wanted%20the%20play%20to%20tour%20around%20Karnataka.%20The%20Punjabi%20language%20show%20%E2%80%9Cended%20up%20performing%20not%20only%20in%20Bangalore%20and%20Mysore%20but%20also%20in%20cities%20like%20Udupi%2C%20Heggodu%20and%20Dharwad%20to%20receptive%20audiences.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%202005%2C%20I%20revisited%20the%20play%20and%20once%20again%20in%202014%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20director%20wrote%2C%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20each%20time%20it%20spoke%20to%20me%20afresh.%E2%80%9D%20The%20published%20edition%20of%20%3Cem%3ENagamandala%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20from%20OUP%2C%20still%20uses%20pictures%20from%20the%20early%20shows%20on%20its%20cover.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20414px)%2085vw%2C%20414px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F03125818%2Funnamed.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22414%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F03125818%2Funnamed.jpg%20414w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F03125818%2Funnamed-185x300.jpg%20185w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-699898%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22670%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERamanjeet%20as%20Rani%20in%20Neelam%20Mansingh%20Chowdhry%E2%80%99s%20Naga%20Chhaya%20(1990).%20Courtesy%20Oxford%20University%20Press.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20those%20years%2C%20the%20German%20director%20Fritz%20Bennewitz%20was%20working%20at%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Shri%20Ram%20Centre.%20He%20read%20the%20play%20and%20fired%20off%20a%20postcard%20to%20Karnad%3A%20%E2%80%9CWE%20HAVE%20TO%20DO%20NAGA-MANDALA%2C%20believe%20me%3A%20%E2%80%94%20I%20was%20in%20tears.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F03130009%2Funnamed-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F03130009%2Funnamed-1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F03130009%2Funnamed-1-300x180.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F03130009%2Funnamed-1-1024x615.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-699899%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22721%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECourtesy%20Ashoka%20Archives%20of%20Contemporary%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBennewitz%2C%20who%20frequently%20collaborated%20with%20Vijaya%20Mehta%2C%20sent%20the%20script%20to%20her%20in%20Mumbai.%20Mehta%20decided%20to%20direct%20a%20pilot%20production%20at%20the%20National%20Centre%20for%20Performing%20Arts%2C%20and%20then%20to%20co-direct%20it%20with%20Bennewitz%20at%20the%20upcoming%20Festival%20of%20India%20in%20Germany.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20obstacle%20was%20Karnad%E2%80%99s%20close%20friend%20and%20creative%20accomplice%2C%20Satyadev%20Dubey.%20Without%20ever%20asking%20for%20permission%2C%20he%20had%20made%20an%20announcement%20to%20the%20press%3A%20that%20he%20would%20stage%20%3Cem%3ENagamandala%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20Hindi%20and%20English.%20Karnad%20had%20promised%20Mehta%20the%20rights%20in%20both%20languages.%20This%20led%20to%20a%20heated%20exchange%20of%20letters%20(preserved%20in%20Karnad%E2%80%99s%20archives%20at%20the%20Ashoka%20University).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDubey%2C%20defying%20calls%20to%20see%20reason%2C%20eventually%20wrote%20to%20his%20friend%3A%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20a%20trial%20of%20strength.%20You%20may%20side%20with%20her%20if%20you%20wish.%20Try%20stopping%20me.%20I%20am%20not%20logical%20%E2%80%93%20I%20am%20Satyadev%20Dubey.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F03130107%2Funnamed-2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F03130107%2Funnamed-2.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F03130107%2Funnamed-2-300x208.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F03130107%2Funnamed-2-1024x708.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-699900%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22830%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECourtesy%20Ashoka%20Archives%20of%20Contemporary%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20Karnad%20prevailed.%20In%20her%20autobiography%20%3Cem%3EJhimma%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2013)%2C%20Mehta%20recalled%20three%20moments%20that%20stunned%20the%20audience%20during%20her%201991%20run.%20These%20passages%20were%20generously%20translated%20for%20us%20by%20Shanta%20Gokhale.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20moment%20was%20the%20opening%20scene%20of%20the%20play%2C%20as%20seventy%20or%20eighty%20twinkling%20oil%20lamps%20enter%20a%20dark%20stage.%20The%20next%20was%20the%20union%20of%20Rani%20and%20Nagaraj%2C%20%E2%80%9Cplayed%20out%20against%20the%20fervour%20and%20beat%20of%20an%20Adivasi%20song%E2%80%9D%2C%20as%20their%20bodies%20twisted%2C%20turned%20and%20wound%20around%20each%20other%20without%20touching.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20third%20scene%20that%20continued%20to%20haunt%20the%20audience%20was%20the%20Naga-pariksha%2C%20ordeal%20by%20snake%20venom.%20When%20Rani%20agreed%20to%20face%20the%20challenge%2C%20a%20deep%2C%20sombre%20chant%20of%20Om%20began.%20The%20collective%20voice%20of%20the%20villagers%20gathered%20around%20her%20was%20like%20the%20drone%20of%20a%20strummed%20tanpura%2C%20adding%20a%20sense%20of%20mystery%20to%20the%20event.%20The%20soft%20thumping%20of%20a%20drum%20joined%20in.%20Rani%20approached%20the%20totem%20pole%2C%20moved%20forward%2C%20recoiled%2C%20but%20then%20walked%20back%20and%20plunged%20her%20hand%20into%20the%20snake%20hole%20at%20the%20foot%20of%20the%20pole.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESomething%20seemed%20to%20be%20pulling%20her%20hand%20down.%20She%20struggled%20to%20free%20it.%20When%20she%20finally%20managed%20to%20pull%20her%20hand%20out%2C%20it%20had%20turned%20into%20the%20hood%20of%20a%20cobra.%20She%20stared%20fixedly%20at%20it.%20The%20cobra%20hood%20came%20close%20to%20her%20face%2C%20slid%20around%20her%20neck%20as%20though%20to%20sting%20her%2C%20but%20caressed%20her%20instead%2C%20and%20slowly%20slithered%20down%20her%20body%20and%20disappeared.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20then%20the%20chanting%20and%20drumming%20had%20reached%20a%20crescendo.%20At%20this%20point%2C%20it%20stopped.%20There%20was%20a%20jubilant%20shout.%20The%20villagers%20hailed%20Rani%20as%20a%20goddess.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMehta%E2%80%99s%201991%20production%20at%20the%20NCPA%20starred%20Bhakti%20Barve%20as%20Kurudavva%2C%20Sukanya%20Kulkarni%20as%20Rani%2C%20Sanjay%20Belose%20and%20Ganesh%20Yadav%2C%20and%20proved%20a%20runaway%20success%20in%20Mumbai.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F03132158%2Funnamed-17.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F03132158%2Funnamed-17.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-con