%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fsimultaneous-elections-why-now%5C%22%3ESimultaneous%20Elections%3A%20Why%20Now%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20double-edged%20recommendation%20from%20the%20Law%20Commission%20and%20the%20Kovind%20committee%20is%20obviously%20planned%20as%20a%20strategic%20poll-eve%20declaration%2C%20to%20ensure%20that%20this%20grossly%20populist%20and%20anti-democratic%20step%2C%20emerges%20as%20one%20of%20the%20foremost%20politically%20polarising%20issues%2C%20to%20benefit%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20in%20the%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20project%2C%20one%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20favourite%20missions%2C%20was%20pushed%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20a%20quartet%20of%20questionable%20%E2%80%98justifications%E2%80%99%3A%20excessive%20expenditure%20for%20holding%20polls%20in%20rapid%20succession%3B%20impediments%20to%20governance%20because%20of%20Model%20Code%20of%20Conduct%20(MCC)%3B%20impact%20on%20the%20delivery%20of%20essential%20services%3B%20and%20undue%20burden%20on%20government%20personnel%20deployed%20for%20conducting%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20these%20issues%2C%20flagged%20consistently%20by%20Modi%20and%20his%20party%20to%20run%20down%20regular%20elections%2C%20at%20least%20the%20two%20politically%20contentious%20ones%20%E2%80%93%20a%20hindrance%20to%20governance%20after%20the%20MCC%20comes%20into%20play%20frequently%20and%20impeding%20the%20delivery%20of%20fundamental%20services%2C%20can%20be%20resolved%20by%20open-ended%20discussion%20between%20political%20parties%20and%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20government%20made%20no%20effort%20to%20secure%20bipartisan%20support%20for%20the%20plan%20after%20March%202016%2C%20when%20Modi%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics-and-nation%2Fpm-narendra-modi-keen-on-simultaneous-lok-sabha-assembly-polls%2Farticleshow%2F51618833.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Eadvocated%3C%2Fa%3E%20simultaneous%20elections%20to%20panchayat%20bodies%2C%20assemblies%20and%20parliament%20while%20addressing%20BJP%20national%20office-bearers%20and%20state%20unit%20chiefs.%20Prior%20to%20this%2C%20the%20issue%20remained%20one%20of%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20numerous%20electoral%20promises%20made%20in%20its%20manifesto%20from%201984%20onwards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202023%2C%20the%20government%20abruptly%20appointed%20the%20Kovind%20Committee%20and%20it%20nominated%20Congress%20leader%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Chowdhury%20without%20his%20consent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F16163914%2F2048px-BMC_Election_2012_-_Ink_mark_after_voting_6886404209.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F16163914%2F2048px-BMC_Election_2012_-_Ink_mark_after_voting_6886404209.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F16163914%2F2048px-BMC_Election_2012_-_Ink_mark_after_voting_6886404209-300x200.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F16163914%2F2048px-BMC_Election_2012_-_Ink_mark_after_voting_6886404209-1024x683.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-636461%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPhoto%3A%20Yogesh%20Mhatre%2FCC%20BY%202.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20he%20opted%20out%20questioning%20the%20Committee%E2%80%99s%20composition%2C%20contending%20that%20its%20conclusion%20was%20pre-determined.%20Importantly%2C%20in%20his%20first%20address%20as%20president%20of%20India%20to%20the%20two%20Houses%20of%20Parliament%20in%20January%202018%2C%20Kovind%20made%20a%20strong%20pitch%20for%20simultaneous%20elections%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20assemblies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20speech%20began%20the%20practice%20of%20the%20president%20putting%20a%20stamp%20of%20approval%20on%20assertions%20made%20by%20the%20PM.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20Kovind%20cannot%20be%20been%20expected%20to%20take%20a%20contrary%20position%2C%20rendering%20the%20Committee%20into%20an%20eyewash%2C%20aimed%20at%20camouflaging%20a%20pre-decided%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20examining%20ways%20to%20overcome%20hurdles%20in%20governance%20posed%20by%20the%20MCC%20and%20reducing%20the%20burden%20on%20personnel%20for%20electioneering%2C%20the%20BJP%20also%20took%20little%20action%20in%20curtailing%20poll%20expenditure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%20nullifying%20electoral%20bonds%20triggered%20a%20fresh%20round%20of%20debate%20on%20curbing%20poll%20expenditure.%20It%20again%20underscored%20minimal%20efforts%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20Centre%20to%20rein%20in%20poll%20costs%20to%20ensure%20a%20level%20playing%20field%20for%20all%20parties%20and%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20ambiguity%20that%20the%20reasons%20cited%20by%20the%20Modi-BJP%20combine%20while%20pursuing%20the%20One%20Nation%20One%20Election%20undertaking%20are%20essentially%20a%20composite%20smokescreen%20to%20hide%20the%20real%20motivation%20behind%20simultaneous%20elections.%20This%20move%20will%20negatively%20impact%20the%20Indian%20body%20politic%20once%20it%20becomes%20the%20norm%20if%20the%20BJP%20is%20elected%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20long-held%20view%20that%20in%20a%20politically%20diverse%20nation%20like%20India%2C%20periodic%20elections%20ensure%20that%20no%20emotionally%20driven%20mandate%20grants%20absolute%20power%20to%20a%20single%20party.%20It%20is%20necessary%20for%20voters%20to%20be%20armed%20with%20a%20corrective%20device%20and%20frequent%20elections%20not%20just%20%E2%80%98rectify%E2%80%99%20verdicts%2C%20but%20also%20keep%20parties%20and%20governments%20on%20their%20toes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20if%20each%20and%20every%20state%20election%20was%20held%20alongside%20the%20parliamentary%20poll%20held%20after%20Indira%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20assassination%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20political%20history%20would%20have%20been%20different%20and%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20may%20have%20continued%20in%20office%20well%20beyond%201989%20when%20his%20government%20was%20voted%20out.%20Likewise%20in%202019%20when%20the%20twin%20Pulwama-Balakot%20events%20boosted%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20fortunes%20and%20gave%20it%20a%20mandate%20that%20was%20improbable%20previously.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20think-tank%2C%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies%2C%20a%20bipartisan%2C%20nonprofit%20policy%20research%20organisation%20hypothesised%20that%20if%20simultaneous%20elections%20were%20held%20in%20all%20states%20simultaneously%20with%20the%202014%20parliamentary%20poll%2C%20the%20BJP%20would%20have%20met%20with%20greater%20success%20in%20the%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcasi.sas.upenn.edu%2Fiit%2Fbalasubramaniam-bhatiya-das%5C%22%3Epaper%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20by%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%E2%80%99s%20Centre%20for%20the%20Advanced%20Study%20of%20India%20in%202020%20empirically%20demonstrated%20that%20voters%20in%20simultaneous%20elections%20were%20more%20swayed%20by%20party%20affiliation%20over%20the%20candidate%E2%80%99s%20individual%20characteristics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResearchers%20also%20established%20that%20the%20probability%20of%20candidates%20from%20the%20same%20party%20winning%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20Assembly%20seats%2C%20when%20held%20simultaneously%2C%20rises%20by%20more%20than%2020%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20insidious%20move%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20these%20studies%2C%20highlighting%20that%20reasons%20advanced%20for%20ushering%20simultaneous%20polls%20are%20little%20but%20ruses%2C%20the%20government%20has%20also%20refused%20to%20learn%20from%20the%20experience%20of%20the%20United%20Kingdom%20which%20in%20March%202022%20repealed%20the%20Fixed-term%20Parliaments%20Act%2C%202011%20after%20all%20parties%20concluded%20that%20this%20legislation%2C%20resulted%20in%20chaos%20and%20constitutional%20deadlock%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20ignoramus%20within%20the%20government%20and%20the%20BJP%2C%20The%20Dissolution%20and%20Calling%20of%20Parliament%20Bill%20was%20introduced%20on%20May%2012%2C%202021%2C%20and%20it%20received%20Royal%20Assent%20on%20March%2024%2C%202022.%20The%20passage%20of%20this%20Act%20put%20an%20end%20to%20rather%20%E2%80%98adventurous%E2%80%99%202011%20legislation%20that%20fixed%20the%20time%20between%20two%20parliamentary%20elections%20as%20against%20the%20tried-and-tested%20and%20democratic%20way%20of%20holding%20elections%2C%20the%20way%20it%20was%20called%20for%20generations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20British%20law%20of%202011%20that%20has%20now%20been%20repealed%20pertained%20only%20for%20the%20UK%E2%80%99s%20general%20elections%2C%20and%20not%20for%20polls%20at%20the%20national%20and%20state%20level%20as%20being%20contemplated%2C%20its%20nullification%20has%20lessons%20for%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Flaw-commission-may-suggest-new-chapter-in-constitution-on-one-nation-one-election%5C%22%3ELaw%20Commission%20May%20Suggest%20New%20Chapter%20in%20Constitution%20on%20%E2%80%98One%20Nation%2C%20One%20Election%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20thereby%20be%20prudent%20to%20press%20for%20greater%20circumspection%20and%20debate%20and%20not%20rush%20through%20the%20process%20of%20simultaneously%20holding%20polls%20at%20every%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20the%20way%20that%20the%20FTPA%20of%202011%20significantly%20affected%20the%20British%20constitution%2C%20the%20proposed%20changes%20in%20the%20Indian%20constitution%20to%20usher%20in%20simultaneous%20polls%20would%20hollow%20out%20the%20spirit%20of%20Indian%20tenets%2C%20showcased%20by%20Modi%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Conly%20Holy%20Book.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%E2%80%9Cthree%20major%20Constitutional%20amendments%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20would%20be%20required%20to%20usher%20in%20the%20proposed%20%E2%80%98fixed%E2%80%99%20electoral%20calendar%2C%20would%20also%20necessitate%20the%20insertion%20of%20an%20additional%20chapter%20in%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20importantly%2C%20the%20tenures%20of%20several%20state%20assemblies%20would%20either%20have%20to%20be%20curtailed%20or%20extended%20between%202024%20and%202029%20to%20ensure%20that%20when%20the%20next%20parliamentary%20poll%20is%20held%2C%20all%20state%20assemblies%20are%20also%20dissolved%20and%20elections%20conducted%20simultaneously.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20tenure-adjustment%20will%20violate%20the%20people%E2%80%99s%20mandates%20in%20these%20states%20because%20it%20was%20for%20a%20specified%20period%20which%20could%20be%20altered%20only%20due%20to%20political%20exigencies%20like%20the%20government%20losing%20majority%20due%20to%20desertions%2C%20or%20being%20voted%20out%20through%20a%20no-confidence%20motion.%20In%20theory%2C%20these%20acts%20reflect%20public%20sentiment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20amendments%20also%20mandate%20that%20in%20the%20event%20of%20governments%20losing%20majority%2C%20efforts%20should%20be%20made%20for%20the%20formation%20of%20either%20a%20%E2%80%98unity%E2%80%99%20government%20or%20electing%20a%20new%20government%20for%20a%20curtailed%20period%20till%20the%20next%20%E2%80%98scheduled%E2%80%99%20poll.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20the%20proposals%20that%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20mooted%20are%20aimed%20at%20strengthening%20Indian%20democracy%20and%20institutions.%20Instead%2C%20the%20effort%20is%20to%20ensure%20the%20stability%20of%20the%20Executive%20and%20giving%20greater%20importance%20to%20governance.%20The%20entire%20effort%20is%20aimed%20at%20running%20the%20nation%20like%20a%20corporate%20structure%20and%20not%20a%20democratic%20country%20where%20people%E2%80%99s%20mandate%20is%20supreme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20primary%20intention%20behind%20pushing%20simultaneous%20polls%20is%20to%20weaken%20multi-party%20democracy%20under%20which%20different%20parties%20govern%20in%20states%20and%20replace%20it%20with%20a%20one-party%20system%20with%20absolute%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20would%20also%20put%20a%20de%20facto%20end%20to%20the%20system%20of%20parliamentary%20democracy%20and%20introduce%20a%20presidential%20form%20of%20polity%20wherein%20the%20individual%20is%20of%20greater%20importance%20than%20organisation%20and%20ideology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20need%20to%20quickly%20recollect%20that%20when%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20debated%20if%20India%20should%20retain%20the%20bicameral%20system%20or%20shift%20to%20a%20unicameral%20legislature%2C%20the%20decision%20was%20almost%20unanimously%20to%20retain%20the%20Upper%20House%20because%20it%20provided%20greater%20political%20diversity%20by%20electing%20its%20members%20biennially%20and%20%E2%80%98corrected%E2%80%99%20political%20spikes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20just%20the%20opposition%20parties%20but%20even%20political%20allies%20of%20the%20BJP%20must%20be%20aware%20of%20the%20threat%20to%20their%20existence%20as%20over%20time%2C%20simultaneous%20polls%20will%20weaken%20India%E2%80%99s%20regional%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20can%20disagree%20with%20the%20politics%20of%20several%20of%20these%2C%20but%20few%20can%20deny%20that%20the%20emergence%20of%20regional%20forces%20empowered%20new%20communities%2C%20previously%20excluded%20from%20the%20power%20structure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPushing%20through%20One%20Nation%20One%20Election%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20parliamentary%20election%20is%20an%20insidious%20move%20and%20must%20be%20opposed%20by%20all%20democratic%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENilanjan%20Mukhopadhyay%20is%20an%20author%20and%20journalist%20based%20in%20Delhi-NCR.%20His%20latest%20book%20is%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%98The%20Demolition%2C%20The%20Verdict%20and%20The%20Temple%3A%20The%20Definitive%20Book%20on%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20Project%2C%3Cem%3E%20and%20he%E2%80%99s%20also%20the%20author%20of%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%98Narendra%20Modi%3A%20The%20Man%2C%20The%20Times%E2%80%99.%20%3Cem%3EHis%20X%20handle%20is%20%40NilanjanUdwin%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709447297000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26110403%2FThe-Wire-56.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwhy-simultaneous-polls-may-reduce-india-to-worlds-largest-democracy-only-in-name%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20primary%20intention%20behind%20pushing%20simultaneous%20polls%20is%20to%20weaken%20multi-party%20democracy%20under%20which%20different%20parties%20govern%20in%20states%20and%20replace%20it%20with%20a%20one-party%20system%20with%20absolute%20power.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwhy-simultaneous-polls-may-reduce-india-to-worlds-largest-democracy-only-in-name%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BIf%20You%20Don't%20Value...%26quot%3B%3A%20Ex-Pakistan%20Star's%20Blunt%20Take%20On%20Kishan-Iyer%20Row%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20dropping%20of%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Shreyas%20Iyer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Fplayers%2F64384-shreyas-santosh-iyer-playerprofile%5C%22%3EShreyas%20Iyer%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Ishan%20Kishan%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Fplayers%2F107047-ishan-kishan-playerprofile%5C%22%3EIshan%20Kishan%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%